Description: CVE-2026-6473 - Fix integer overflow vulnerabilities in PostgreSQL
 Multiple integer overflow vulnerabilities allow authenticated users to cause
 out-of-bounds memory writes via crafted inputs to various database functions
 including ts_headline(), ltree lquery parsing, array_agg(), regex operations,
 and formatting functions. This patch introduces overflow-safe allocation
 macros (palloc_array, palloc0_array, repalloc_array) and fixes all known
 overflow sites. Backported from PostgreSQL 14.23 fix commits to PG13.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/postgres/postgres/commit/46593aea0a5ca7ead0876833d99639c9a4bb5a9d
