Description: CVE-2026-6477 - Fix stack buffer overwrite in libpq PQfn
 When result_is_int is set to 0, PQfn() cannot validate that the result
 fits in result_buf, so it will write data beyond the end of the buffer
 when the server returns more data than requested. Add a buf_size
 parameter to pqFunctionCall3() that is used to protect against overruns,
 and use it in a private version of PQfn() (PQnfn) that also accepts a
 buf_size parameter. The frontend large object interface (lo_read,
 lo_lseek64, lo_tell64) now uses PQnfn with proper buffer sizes.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/postgres/postgres/commit/8ac723b2bc992fd86b09ae73c7c610242c4c037e
Author: Nathan Bossart <nathan@postgresql.org>
Last-Update: 2026-05-19

